            <thetext>On the latest update of the CLDR data in the framework, we figured out that our parser for data formats does only accept years with two or four digits. 
But there can also be date formats with one or even more than four digits. (http://unicode.org/reports/tr35/#Date_Format_Patterns) 
So the parser should be fixed as soon as possible.</thetext>
